Subject: [PATCH] BACKPORT: FROMGIT: media: Add AV1 uAPI

This patch adds the AOMedia Video 1 (AV1) kernel stateless V4L2 decoder uAPI.

This design is based on currently available AV1 API implementations and
aims to support the development of AV1 V4L2 stateless video codecs
on Linux.

This is extracted from v7 patch by Daniel Almeida [1], which was merged
to the media-stage tree [2] as commit 9de30f579980 ("media: Add AV1 uAPI"),
and considered to be the final version.

The definitions are kept in this separate file instead of merged into
`include/uapi/linux/videodev2.h` and `include/uapi/linux/v4l2-controls.h`
to avoid possible conflicts with the other header file changes. A
separate file also provides an easier migration path for components
using these definitions.

[1] https://lore.kernel.org/linux-media/20230306161850.492072-1-daniel.almeida@collabora.com/
[2] https://git.linuxtv.org/media_stage.git/commit/?id=9de30f579980b498606a9c2440b73ae3b670771b

